        <div type="recipe">
        <p> Lay your Tongues twelve Days in common Salt and Salt-Petre, then boil them very tender, and blanch them; cut off the Roots, and lay them into a Pot; pour over them a Pickle made of good white Wine Vinegar, which boil up with Pepper, Cloves, Mace, and a little Ginger. When it is ready to take off the Fire, throw in a Piece of Lemon Peel, and three or four Bay-leaves; put it to the Tongues when cold, and tie them up close from the Air. A little of the Pickle with good Oil is their <objectName ref="#sauce">Sauce</objectName>. </p>
            </div>
